paragraphs.title: Welcome to AIA
paragraphs.text: This is a live tutorial, you can run the code yourself. Recommended is to run paragraph by paragraph, you can click on the 'play' button in each paragraph or use shortcut <shift>+<Enter>. also you can run all by clicking 'play' button above. Please check the PREREQUITES paragraph before any execution.

paragraphs.title: INTRODUCTION
paragraphs.text:
%md
*This tutorial uses [BPS](http://analytics.ericsson.se/#/Products) based flink streaming application to receive data from kafka and dump to local file system. AIA PaaSManager is used to deploy the application as a service.*

![Flink streaming application example picture](http://analytics.ericsson.se:23307/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/flink_streaming_app_example.png)

**The following are based on example(/home/cloud-user/example/flink-streaming-example-app) provided in sandbox. This turtorial is provided as a quick start executed in zeppelin, please follow the README.md in application folder for detailed instruction.**

*The example is created using [AIA portal application builder](http://analytics.ericsson.se/#/GetStarted/ecosystem/appbuilder/applications) and the following files(relative path to the application folder) need to be added or modified to achieve the funcationalty*
1. flow.xml: flow descriptor used by BPS for work flow. Please check **_FLOW DESCRIPTOR_** for file content
2. src/main/java/com/ericsson/component/aia/services/bps/flink/test/app/FlinkStreamingExampleApp.java: flink driver class. Please check **_FLINK STREAMING DRIVER CLASS_** for details
3. pba.json: PaaS deployment descriptor. Please check **_PBA DESCRIPTOR_** for details.

  1. flow.xml: flow descriptor used by BPS for work flow. Please check FLOW DESCRIPTOR for file content
  2. src/main/java/com/ericsson/component/aia/services/bps/flink/test/app/FlinkStreamingExampleApp.java: flink driver class. Please check FLINK STREAMING DRIVER CLASS for details
  3. pba.json: PaaS deployment descriptor. Please check PBA DESCRIPTOR for details.

paragraphs.title: PREREQUITES
paragraphs.text:
%md
Please run the **_BPS based spark streaming example_ NOTEBOOK** first, which provide the kafka input for this tutorial.

result.msg: Please run the BPS based spark streaming example NOTEBOOK first, which provide the kafka input for this tutorial.

paragraphs.title: STEP
paragraphs.text:
%md
1. Please follow the **_CLEAN OUTPUT FILE_ paragraph** to clean the output.

2. Please follow the **_BUILD APPLICATION PROJECT_ paragraph** to build the maven based application.

3. Data source is provided as north bound interface in the **_BPS based spark streaming example_ NOTEBOOK**

4. There are several ways to run the application, please follow one of the following modes to run the application. **NOTE:** You need to 'Enable run' in the paragraphs, and cluster mode is used by default here.

  4.1. Please follow the **_STOP EXISTING EXECUTION_ & _START IN LOCAL MODE_** paragraphs to start the flink streaming application.
  4.2. Please follow the **_STOP STANDALONE FLINK JOB_ & _START STANDALONE FLINK JOB_** paragraphs to start the application with standalone flink job manager.
  4.3. Please follow the **_STOP APPLICATION IN CLUSTER_MODE_ & _START APPLICATION IN CLUSTER MODE_** paragraphs to start te application in cluster mode. 

5. Please follow the **_SIMULATE SOME WEB ACCESS ACTION_** paragraph to simulate some web access action, Or you can visit the landing page of this sandbox.

6. Please follow the **_CHECK OUTPUT FILE_** paragraph to check the output file.

  5. Please follow the SIMULATE SOME WEB ACCESS ACTION paragraph to simulate some web access action, Or you can visit the landing page of this sandbox.

  6. Please follow the CHECK OUTPUT FILE paragraph to check the output file.

paragraphs.title: BUILD APPLICATION PROJECT
paragraphs.text:
%sh
sudo -u cloud-user -i mvn clean install -f /home/cloud-user/example/flink-streaming-example-app/pom.xml >> /tmp/flink_streaming_app_example.log
sleep 1m

paragraphs.title: STOP EXISTING EXECUTION
paragraphs.text:
%sh
ps -ef | grep -v grep | grep "java -jar /home/cloud-user/example/flink-streaming-example-app/target/aia-flink-streaming-deployable.jar /home/cloud-user/example/flink-streaming-example-app/flow.xml" | awk '{print $2}' | xargs -I {} kill -9 {}

paragraphs.title: STOP STANDALONE FLINK JOB
paragraphs.text:
%sh
echo "Stopping any running example job"
/opt/flink/bin/flink list | grep FlinkStreamingExampleApp | awk -F " : " '{print $2}' | xargs -I {} /opt/flink/bin/flink cancel {}
sleep 1m

result.msg:

paragraphs.title: START STANDALONE FLINK JOB
paragraphs.text:
%sh
echo "Starting the example application in standalone flink job manager"
/opt/flink/bin/flink run -d /home/cloud-user/example/flink-streaming-example-app/target/aia-flink-streaming-deployable.jar /home/cloud-user/example/flink-streaming-example-app/flow.xml

paragraphs.title: DOCKERIZE THE APPLICATION
paragraphs.text:
%sh
echo "Dockerizing the application and push to local docker registry."
cd /home/cloud-user/example/flink-streaming-example-app
docker build -t localhost:5000/aia/aia-flink-streaming-example-app:1.0.1 . >> /tmp/flink-streaming-example-app.log
docker push localhost:5000/aia/aia-flink-streaming-example-app:1.0.1 >> /tmp/flink-streaming-example-app.log

result.msg: Dockerizing the application and push to local docker registry.

paragraphs.title: UNDEPLOY WITH PAASMANAGER
paragraphs.text:
%sh
echo "Undeploying the application with PaaS manager"
curl -X DELETE http://localhost:8888/paas/v1/applications --data @/home/cloud-user/example/flink-streaming-example-app/pba.json -H "Content-Type: application/json"

echo "Stopping any running example job"
/opt/flink/bin/flink list | grep FlinkStreamingExampleApp | awk -F " : " '{print $2}' | xargs -I {} /opt/flink/bin/flink cancel {}
sleep 1m
